SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: NATPE MONITORS THE GRANTS TO ITS SISTER COMPANY TO ENSURE THAT THE GRANTS ARE USED FOR ITS EXEMPT PURPOSE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 6
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ASSOCIATION IS ORGANIZED INTO A SINGLE CLASS OF VOTING MEMBERS(THE "MEMBERS"). ALL EXHIBITORS AND PAYING ATTENDEES AT THE ASSOCIATION'S EVENTS (INCLUDING, WITHOUT LIMITATION, THE ANNUAL CONVENTION AND MARKETPLACE) SHALL BE ELIGIBLE TO JOIN THE ASSOCIATION AS MEMBERS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: AT LEAST THIRTY PERCENT (30%) OF THE MEMBERS SHALL BE REQUIRED TO APPROVE (I) ANY MERGER OR CONSOLIDATION OF THE ASSOCIATION OR (II) ANY SALE, LEASE, OR EXCHANGE OF ALL OR SUBSTANTIALLY ALL OF THE ASSETS OF THE ASSOCIATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: AN EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE MORE CLOSELY MONITORS THE BUSINESS THAN THE FULL BOARD.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: IN ACCORDANCE WITH NATPE'S CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AT LEAST EACH YEAR, ALL DIRECTORS, OFFICERS AND KEY EMPLOYEES OF NATPE ARE ASKED TO COMPLETE AND SIGN A "DISCLOSURE QUESTIONNAIRE" FOR ANY POTENTIAL CONFLICTS AND THEN UPDATE IF ANY ARISE AFTER COMPLETING THE FORM. IF A CONFLICT OF INTEREST IS REPORTED, THE MATTER WOULD BE REVIEWED AMONGST THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE. THERE IS SOME DISCRETION PROVIDED AS TO HOW IT WOULD BE HANDLED. IF THE CONFLICT IS IDENTIFIED TO EXIST, THE PARTY WITH THE CONFLICT WOULD NOT PARTICIPATE IN DELIBERATIONS AND DECISIONS RELATED TO THE CONFLICT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: NATPE'S EXECUTIVE COMPENSATION REVIEW PROCESS IS ADMINISTERED BY THE COMPENSATION COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD. THE COMPENSATION COMMITTEE IS RESPONSIBLE FOR ESTABLISHING AND MAINTAINING A COMPETITIVE COMPENSATION PROGRAM FOR THE KEY EXECUTIVES OF THE ORGANIZATION. THE COMMITTEE MEETS AS NEEDED TO REVIEW THE COMPENSATION PROGRAM AND MAKES RECOMMENDATIONS FOR ANY CHANGES TO THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE AS APPROPRIATE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: NATPE'S GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
